 Port Elizabeth - The Family Violence Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit in Port Elizabeth is urgently trying to trace the whereabouts of an 8-year-old boy from Barcelona in Gelvandale. According to police information, Recolin Keagan Witbooi was last seen at 13:30 on Saturday afternoon playing with friends in Uranus Street. "He did not go back home. He is also living in Uranus Street," described police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "He was wearing a black hoodie top, black track suit pants and a pair of white Nike takkies." She said anyone, who may have seen him or may know of his whereabouts is asked to contact D/Sgt Luzuko Pehlo on 082 565 0155 or 041 401 3000 or Crime Stop 08600 10111 or their nearest police station. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 